        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare autoimmune bullous skin diseases characterized by painful flaccid blisters and erosions of the oral mucosa predominantly involving the buccal area and with or without extension to the epidermis. Mucosa of the larynx oesophagus conjunctiva nose genitalia and anus are less frequently affected."
        },
